Bank Leumi USA, the U.S. unit of
Israelâ€™s largest lender, said Chief Executive Officer  Uzi Rosen 
retired and was replaced by  Itzhak Eyal , who started at Leumi
Group 35 years ago.  Rosen, 66, was CEO for six years and spent 28 years at Tel
Aviv-based Leumi Group. Eyal, 63, began as an auditor with Leumi
Group and was most recently CEO of Arab Israel Bank in Israel,
the lender said in a statement today.  Bank Leumi USA is the largest subsidiary of Leumi Group,
founded in 1902. The U.S. unit provides financial services to
middle- and upper-middle-market firms, international businesses,
and non-profit organizations through offices in New York,
Illinois, California and Florida, the company said.  The U.S. unit, based in New York, held $5.3 billion in
assets and reported net income of $5 million in the three months
ended June 30.  To contact the reporter on this story:
